headline.main: ARCHANGEL NEWS IRKS WHITE HOUSE; Maritime Commission Rebuked for Announcement of Change in Route to Russia

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Oct. 23 -- The Maritime Commission was publicly rebuked at the White House today for having announced that hence-forth all shipments of war supplies from the United States to Soviet Russia would depart from the port of Boston.
abstract: White House rebukes comm for announcement; State Dept denies Japan influenced course
